HEADWORD: Noyau
<hw>Noy`au"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., prop., the
stone or nut of a fruit, fr. L. <ets>nucalis</ets> like a nut. See
<er>Newel</er> a post.]</ety> <def>A cordial of brandy, etc., flavored
with the kernel of the bitter almond, or of the peach stone,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

